/*
ðŸ’¡ Problem: Smallest Number Greater Than or Equal to n by Powers of Two

ðŸ” Description:
You are given an integer n. Starting from x = 1, repeatedly double a value t (starting at 1) 
and add it to x until x becomes greater than or equal to n. 
Your task is to return the final value of x.

ðŸ“¥ Input:
- A single integer n

ðŸ“¤ Output:
- The smallest value of x such that after the given operations, x >= n.

ðŸ§© Example:
Input:
10
Process:
x = 1, t = 1
t = 2, x = 3
t = 4, x = 7
t = 8, x = 15 (â‰¥ 10, stop)
Output:
15

ðŸ•’ Time Complexity: O(log n)
ðŸ’¾ Space Complexity: O(1)
*/

class Solution {
    public int smallestNumber(int n) {
        int x = 1;
        int t = 1;
        while (x < n) {
            t = t * 2;
            x += t;
        }
        return x;
    }
}
